Package cetus.hir

Class NullStatement

  • java.lang.Object
    • cetus.hir.Statement
      • cetus.hir.NullStatement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Annotatable, Printable, Traversable, java.lang.Cloneable
    public class NullStatement
extends Statement
    Represents an empty statement. Empty statements need to be preserved by the IR because there are some coding "tricks" that rely on them. For example, because a label must appear before a statement, there is no way of putting a label at the end of a block, so it's common to find a labeled null statement there.
